<section>
    <h2>About the Book</h2>
    <p>"The Secret History" is a novel by Donna Tartt, published in 1992. It follows a group of classics students at an elite college in Vermont, and their involvement in a murder plot that spirals out of control.</p>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Characters</h2>
    <p>The main characters in "The Secret History" include:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Richard Papen</li>
        <li>Henry Winter</li>
        <li>Charles Macaulay</li>
        <li>Francis Abernathy</li>
        <li>Bunny Corcoran</li>
        <li>Camilla Macaulay</li>
    </ul>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>Reviews</h2>
    <p>"The Secret History" has received widespread critical acclaim for its rich character development, compelling narrative, and exploration of themes such as morality, guilt, and the nature of friendship.</p>
